         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <persName>
                  <name key="Σώστρατος">Σώστρατος</name> ∶ <name type="patronymic" key="Τεισάνδρο">Τεισάνδρο</name> ∶ <name type="demotic" key="Παιανιεύς">Παιανιεύς</name>
               </persName>.
                </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Sostratus, son of Teisandrus, of Paiania.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The inscription gives the dedicatee name in the nominative, with his patronymic and
                    demotic. The style of the stele is unmistakably fourth century Attica. It is
                    reported to have been found in Salamis. The museum label suggests the more
                    specific dating 375-350 BCE. </p>
         </div>
